{{about|the natural number|the emergency telephone number|999 (emergency telephone number)|other uses|999 (disambiguation)}} {{Refimprove|date=June 2016}} '''999''' ('''nine hundred ninety-nine''' or '''nine-nine-nine''') is a [[natural number]] following [[998 (number)|998]] and preceding [[1000 (number)|1000]].{{Infobox number | number = 999 | cardinal = Nine hundred [and] ninety-nine | ordinal text = Nine hundred [and] ninety-ninth | divisor = 1, 3, 9, 27, 37, 111, 333, 999 | unicode = | greek prefix = | latin prefix = }}
==In mathematics== * a [[Harshad number]]. * a [[Kaprekar number]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sloane's A006886 : Kaprekar numbers|url=https://oeis.org/A006886|website=The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences|publisher=OEIS Foundation|accessdate=2016-06-02}}</ref> * a [[repdigit]] in bases 10 and 36. * a [[palindromic number]] in bases 10, 14 (515<sub>14</sub>), and 36 (RR<sub>36</sub>). * the largest 3-digit [[decimal]] [[integer]].
==Symbology and numerology== In [[SubGenius]] [[numerology]] the number 999 represents [[Bob Dobbs]].
==Emergency Number== '''999''' is the number used to contact the Emergency Services in many countries; See [[999 (emergency telephone number)]].
