The '''Levi–Mises equations''' (also called '''flow rules''') describe the relationship between [[Shear stress|stress]] and [[Strain (materials science)|strain]] for an ideal [[Plasticity (physics)|plastic]] [[solid]] where the [[Elasticity (physics)|elastic]] strains are negligible.

The generalized Levy–Mises equation can be written as:

: <math>\frac{\mathbf{d}\varepsilon_1}{\sigma'_1}=\frac{\mathbf{d}\varepsilon_2}
{\sigma'_2}=\frac{\mathbf{d}\varepsilon_3}{\sigma'_3}=\mathbf{d}\lambda</math>

